title: Gunman at large after two Swedes killed in possible Brussels ‘terror’ attack
description: The attack left a soccer stadium on lockdown and a city on alert as police searched for the suspect.

title: How Hamas’s carefully planned Israel attack devolved into a chaotic rampage
description: What began as a highly organized stealth attack soon devolved into a chaotic rampage, underscoring Hamas’s capacity for sophisticated planning and indiscriminate killing.

title: As Putin visits China, new anti-Western coalition turns on Israel
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin and Chinese President Xi Jinping each face challenges at home, but they have linked arms to confront the U.S. and the West.

title: Court settlement would bar separating migrant families as Trump did
description: A court settlement would bar U.S. immigration agents from prosecuting migrant parents traveling with children for illegally entering the United States.

title: U.S. to ease sanctions on Venezuelan oil for freer presidential election
description: The sanctions relief is to be announced after the socialist government of Nicolás Maduro and the U.S.-backed Venezuelan opposition sign a separate agreement in Barbados on Tuesday.

title: Confusion on Gaza-Egypt border over possible cease-fire and aid deal
description: Despite reports of a deal to let dual nationals out and aid into Gaza, Israel and Hamas announced that there would be no cease-fire, dashing the hopes of hundreds.

title: Poland’s opposition jubilant, ruling party wary ahead of final election count
description: An opposition win over Law and Justice would bring a bastion of illiberalism allied with Trump Republicans into line with Europe’s core democracies.

title: Trump sues over Steele dossier, alleging reputational ‘damage and distress’
description: Donald Trump is suing Christopher Steele’s intelligence consultancy following the leak of an explosive dossier containing allegations that Russia had compromising material on Trump.

title: What is UNRWA, the U.N. agency in Gaza struggling to help Palestinians?
description: The United Nations agency for Palestinian refugees, UNRWA, says it is no longer able to provide aid in Gaza as supplies dwindle and strikes continue.

title: North Korea may be sending arms to Russia for Ukraine war, images suggest
description: Russian ships with military links have repeatedly visited a North Korean port in recent months, with the cargo apparently destined for a munitions base on the Ukrainian border.

title: Russia releases four Ukrainian children after mediation by Qatar
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin was accused of war crimes over the forced relocation of Ukrainian children. Qatar’s successful intervention could lead to other reunifications.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Biden warns Israel against occupying Gaza; hospital fuel nearly gone, U.N. says
description: President Biden’s remarks are one of his firmest efforts to signal restraint to Israel as the humanitarian crisis in Gaza approaches critical levels due to aid blocks.

title: Welcome to the new, ‘new’ Middle East
description: In late September, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu heralded a prosperous and connected “New Middle East.” But it turns out the “old” Middle East was impossible to bury.
